note.p:
Pub. L. 109–366, § 8(b), Oct. 17, 2006, 120 Stat. 2636, provided that: “Section 1004 of the Detainee Treatment Act of 2005 (42 U.S.C. 2000dd–1) shall apply with respect to any criminal prosecution that— “(1) relates to the detention and interrogation of aliens described in such section;
“(2) is grounded in section 2441(c)(3) of title 18, United States Code; and
“(3) relates to actions occurring between September 11, 2001, and December 30, 2005.”
